'''Abdessamad''' "'''Abde'''" '''Ezzalzouli''' ({{langx|ar|عبد الصمد الزلزولي}}; born 17 December 2001), sometimes known as '''Ez Abde''', is a Moroccan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left winger]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Real Betis]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

Ezzalzouli began his professional career with [[Hércules CF|Hércules]] in 2019 before signing for [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2021. Following a loan move to [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]], he joined Real Betis in 2023, helping the club to its first ever European final.

Ezzalzouli made his international debut for Morocco in 2022, after previously being [[Cap (sport)|capped]] by the nation's youth teams at [[Morocco national under-20 football team|under-20]] level. He was chosen in the Moroccan squads for the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]] and the [[Africa Cup of Nations]] in [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023]] and [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations|2025]].

==Early life==
Born in [[Beni Mellal]] Morocco, Ezzalzouli moved to Spain with his family at the age of seven to live and started his football youth career in the neighborhood of Carrús, in the city of [[Elche]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lagradaonline.com/primer-equipo/abde|title=Apuntan a un supuesto interés por Abde|date=23 November 2020|website=lagradaonline.com}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Hércules===
Ezzalzouli was part of the youth academies for numerous clubs in the [[Elche]] area, including Peña Ilicitana Raval CF and Promesas Elche CF.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/alicante/deporte/hercules-cf/20210831/abde-pone-rumbo-masia/608439157_0.html|title=Abde pone rumbo a La Masía|date=31 August 2021|website=El Español}}</ref> He trialled at [[Elche CF]], the main club in his hometown, but was not offered a place in their academy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/11/23/mas_futbol/1606158475_770163.html|title=Abde, el niño rebelde que tiene como referente a Neymar|date=23 November 2020|website=AS.com}}</ref> [[Hércules CF B|Hércules B]] coach Antonio Moreno Domínguez offered him a contract, and Ezzalzouli subsequently joined the club in the neighbouring city of [[Alicante]], and began his senior career with the B-team in 2019.
[[File:Barcelona Training Miami 2022 04 (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|Ezzalzouli training with [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2022]]

===Barcelona===
Ezzalzouli transferred to [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona B]] on 31 August 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20211030/1001706790/abde-debuta-mano-sergi.html|title=Abde debuta de la mano de Sergi|date=30 October 2021|website=Mundo Deportivo}}</ref> He made his professional debut with [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in a 1–1 [[La Liga]] draw with [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]] on 30 October 2021, coming on as a substitute in the 80th minute. Ezzalzouli thus became the first Moroccan-born player to feature for Barça's first team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/30/spain/primera-division/futbol-club-barcelona/deportivo-alaves/3530336/|title=Barcelona vs. Alaves – 30 October 2021|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Barcelona against [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]] in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Nico and Ez Abde score first goals for FC Barcelona |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2413084/nico-and-ez-abde-score-first-goals-for-fc-barcelona |access-date=15 March 2022 |website=www.fcbarcelona.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 December 2021 |title=Moroccan-born EZ Abde scores first goal for Barcelona |url=https://www.maghrebmagazine.com/moroccan-born-ez-abde-scores-first-goal-for-barcelona/901/ |access-date=15 March 2022 |website=Maghreb Magazine}}</ref>

====Loan to Osasuna====
{{Quote box|width=31%|align=right|quote=“Abde’s game is spectacular".
 |source =—[[Xavi (footballer, born 1980)|Xavi]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Heavy |first1=sports |title=Xavi Admits He's Surprised By 'Spectacular' Barcelona Teenager |url=https://heavy.com/sports/fc-barcelona/xavi-surprised-by-spectacular-teen/ |access-date=Dec 12, 2021 |publisher=Gill clark}}</ref>}}

In September 2022, he renewed his contract with Barcelona until 2026 and was ensuingly loaned to Osasuna.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20220901/1001860569/abde-renovado-cedido-osasuna.html|website=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|date=1 September 2022|first=Jordi|last=Batalla|title=Abde, renovado y cedido a Osasuna}}</ref> On 4 September, he made his first appearance for Osasuna against [[Rayo Vallecano]] after being subbed in the 81st minute, he managed to assist the winning goal in that game, which ended in a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhan |first=Srinivas |date=4 September 2022 |title=Video: Barcelona youngster grabs stunning assist on debut for loan club |url=https://barcauniversal.com/video-barcelona-youngster-grabs-stunning-assist-on-debut-for-loan-club/ |access-date=7 September 2022 |website=Barca Universal |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Debut dreamed: Abde took and gives him the triumph to the Osasuna |url=http://www.fcbarcelonanoticias.com/en/players/famous-debut-abde-attends-da-triunfo-osasuna_283980_102.html |access-date=7 September 2022 |website=FCBN |date=4 September 2022 |language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=WATCH: Ez Abde conjures up brilliant assist on Osasuna debut |url=https://www.barcablaugranes.com/2022/9/4/23336709/watch-ez-abde-conjures-up-brilliant-assist-on-osasuna-debut |access-date=7 September 2022 |website=www.barcablaugranes.com |date=4 September 2022 |language=en}}</ref>

On 26 January 2023, Ezzalzouli scored his first goal for the club in a 2–1 victory against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the [[2022–23 Copa del Rey|2022–23 Copa del Rey quarter-finals]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-27 |title=Super Osasuna's Copa del Rey fairy tale continues |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/osasuna-esposasuna/story/4862244/how-osasuna-reached-first-copa-del-rey-semifinal-since-2005 |access-date=2023-03-02 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> He scored his first league goal exactly one month later, in a 3–2 win against the same opponent.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-02-26 |title=الزلزولي يمنح أوساسونا الفوز على حساب إشبيلية في مباراة سجل فيها النصيري - هسبورت |language=ar-AR |work=هسبورت |url=https://www.hesport.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B2%D9%84%D8%B2%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AD-%D8%A3%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%88%D8%B2-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8-258059.html |access-date=2023-03-02}}</ref>

===Betis===
On 1 September 2023, Ezzalzouli signed a five-year contract with fellow La Liga club [[Real Betis]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3664527/agreement-with-betis-for-the-transfer-of-ez-abde|title=Agreement with Betis for the transfer of Ez Abde|publisher=FC Barcelona|date=1 September 2023|accessdate=1 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realbetisbalompie.es/noticias/actualidad/abde-nuevo-jugador-del-real-betis-29389|title=Abde, nuevo jugador del Real Betis|trans-title=Abde, new player of Real Betis|publisher=Real Betis|language=es|date=1 September 2023|accessdate=1 September 2023}}</ref> with the transfer being reportedly worth €7.5 million, plus a buy-back option in favor of Barcelona.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lagos |first=Daniel |date=1 September 2023 |title=Oficial: Abde firma por el Betis |url=https://as.com/futbol/primera/abde-cumple-la-hora-de-ruta-n/ |access-date=2 September 2023 |website=Diario AS |language=es-ES}}</ref> On 9 September 2023, Ezzalzouli made his debut in a 5–0 loss against Barcelona.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Barcelona crush Betis to go top |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66834344 |access-date=2023-09-29}}</ref> On 1 October 2023, Ezzalzouli scored his first goal for the team in a 3–0 victory against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Real |first=Mario Reinoso del |date=2023-10-02 |title=Real Betis 3-0 Valencia: resumen, goles y resultado |url=https://as.com/futbol/primera/real-betis-valencia-en-directo-laliga-ea-sports-hoy-en-vivo-n/ |access-date=2023-10-02 |website=Diario AS |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-01 |title=Ezzalzouli shines with a wonderful goal against Valencia in the Spanish League - Heba Sport |url=https://www.hibasport.com/details-262560.html |access-date=2023-10-02 |language=ar}}</ref> On 1 November 2023, Ezzalzouli was nominated for the 2023 African Young Player of the Year by [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-11 |title=CAF announces CAF Awards 2023 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-caf-awards-2023-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=2023-11-01 |website=CAF |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 8 May 2025, Ezzalzouli scored an extra-time goal in a 2–2 second-leg away draw against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] to secure Betis' place in the [[2025 UEFA Conference League final|UEFA Conference League final]], the club's first final in a UEFA competition, by winning 4–3 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/conference-league-fiorentina-2-2-214200504.html |title=Conference League {{!}} Fiorentina 2-2 Real Betis (3-4 agg): No third Final for the Viola |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=8 May 2025 }}</ref> In the final against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], he scored to give Betis the lead, though his side were eventually defeated 4–1.<ref name="ueclfinal"/>

==International career==
Ezzalzouli represented the [[Morocco national under-20 football team|Morocco under-20 team]] at the [[2020 Arab Cup U-20]], scoring two goals in five games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hibasport.com/details-187635.html|title=من مواليد بني ملال.. 5 معلومات عن عبد الصمد الزلزولي الذي التحق بكبار برشلونة - هبة سبور|date=29 October 2021 }}</ref> On 20 December 2021, Abdessamad rejected [[Vahid Halilhodžić]] invitation to represent [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]] in the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] to focus on his club.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2021 AFCON: Barcelona youngster Abde Ezzalzouli rejects Morocco call-up for tournament |url=https://footballghana.com/2021-afcon-barcelona-youngster-abde-ezzalzouli-rejects-morocco-call-up-for-tournament |access-date=15 March 2022 |website=Footballghana |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Player Refusing AFCON Call Up To Focus On Club Commitments |url=https://flipboard.com/article/https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sportbible.com%2Ffootball%2Fplayer-refusing-afcon-call-up-to-focus-on-club-commitments-20211226 |access-date=15 March 2022 |website=Flipboard |language=en}}</ref> He obtained Spanish citizenship in December 2021, holding dual Moroccan and Spanish citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20211228/1001730532/abde-documentos-doble-nacionalidad.html|title=Abde ya tiene los documentos para la doble nacionalidad|date=28 December 2021|website=Mundo Deportivo}}</ref>

On 17 March 2022, Ezzalzouli was listed in the 26-man squad to face [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF third round]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Abdessamad Ezzalzouli sélectionné avec le Maroc pour le barrage contre la RDC |url=https://www.sofoot.com/abdessamad-ezzalzouli-selectionne-avec-le-maroc-pour-le-barrage-contre-la-rdc-512138.html |access-date=17 March 2022 |website=SOFOOT.com |date=17 March 2022 |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=MATIN |first=Abderrahmane Ichi, LE |title=La liste des 26 joueurs de Halihodzic avec Attiah Allah & Ezzalzouli |url=https://lematin.ma/express/2022/liste-26-joueurs-vahid-halihodzic-yahia-attiah-allah-abdessamad-ezzalzouli/373405.html |access-date=17 March 2022 |website=Le Matin |date=17 March 2022 |language=fr}}</ref>

In September 2022, Ezzalzouli was called up to join the Morocco national team.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.facebook.com/ENMAROCofficiel/photos/ms.c.eJw1x8kJACAQBMGMZNyx98g~;MUGwfkVia6srTkiLdyUede1~;QhSeC~_IbCXI~-.bps.a.123756449548237/565330108724200/|title=Équipe du Maroc|date=12 September 2022|access-date=12 September 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=12 September 2022 |title=Hakim Ziyech makes return to World Cup team under Regragui's preselection |url=https://en.hespress.com/49144-hakim-ziyech-makes-return-to-word-cup-team-under-regraguis-selection.html |access-date=24 September 2022 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> He played his first match in a friendly against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] at the [[RCDE Stadium]] in [[Cornellà de Llobregat]], which ended in a 2–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 September 2022 |title=Morocco defeats Chili in friendly game 2-0 |url=https://en.hespress.com/49880-morocco-defeats-chili-in-friendly-game-2-0.html |access-date=24 September 2022 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=24 September 2022 |title=England booed as World Cup prep hits horror eight-year low; Brazil make huge statement |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/world-cup/nations-league-england-vs-italy-brazil-vs-ghana-news-scores-results-world-cup-2022/news-story/2de75e18d5da7378ad99eddd3e664dfa |access-date=24 September 2022 |website=Fox Sports |language=en}}</ref>

On 10 November 2022, he was named in Morocco's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Qatar]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco World Cup 2022 squad: Who's in and who's out? {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=www.goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=10 November 2022 |title=Moroccan coach unveils list of 26 Atlas Lions in 2022 World Cup |url=https://en.hespress.com/52697-moroccan-coach-unveils-list-of-26-atlas-lions-in-2022-world-cup.html |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref>

In June 2023, he was included in the squad for the [[2023 U-23 Africa Cup of Nations]], hosted by Morocco itself;<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 June 2023 |title=Sei bianconeri con le nazionali |url=https://www.fclugano.com/sei-bianconeri-con-le-nazionali-2/ |access-date=27 June 2023 |website=[[FC Lugano]] |language=it-CH |archive-date=27 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240527002315/https://www.fclugano.com/sei-bianconeri-con-le-nazionali-2/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=24 June 2023 |title=تشكيلة المنتخب الوطني لاقل من 23 سنة امام غينيا |url=https://site.frmf.ma/%d8%aa%d8%b4%d9%83%d9%8a%d9%84%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%ae%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%88%d8%b7%d9%86%d9%8a-%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%82%d9%84-%d9%85%d9%86-23-%d8%b3%d9%86%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%85%d8%a7-2/ |access-date=27 June 2023 |website=[[Royal Moroccan Football Federation]] |language=ar}}</ref> named as the team [[Captain (association football)|captain]],<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Leiva |first=Juanma |date=9 July 2023 |title=Abde, héroe nacional |url=https://as.com/futbol/internacional/abde-heroe-nacional-n/ |access-date=9 July 2023 |website=Diario AS |language=es-ES}}</ref> he went on to score three goals<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-24 |title=Morocco stage late rally to defeat Guinea in TotalEnergies U23 AFCON opener {{!}} Total U-23 Africa Cup of Nations 2023 |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-u23-africa-cup-of-nations/2023/news/morocco-stage-late-rally-to-defeat-guinea-in-totalenergies-u23-afcon-opener |access-date=2023-06-28 |website=CAFOnline.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-27 |title=TotalEnergies U23 AFCON: Morocco secure semi-final berth with impressive win over Ghana {{!}} Total U-23 Africa Cup of Nations 2023 |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-u23-africa-cup-of-nations/2023/news/morocco-secure-semi-final-berth-with-impressive-win-over-ghana |access-date=2023-06-28 |website=CAFOnline.com |language=en}}</ref> and three assists in four matches,<ref name=":0" /> as the ''Atlas Lions'' won their first title and qualified for the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite web |date=8 July 2023 |title=Morocco win maiden TotalEnergies U-23 Africa Cup of Nations title with victory over Egypt {{!}} Total U-23 Africa Cup of Nations 2023 |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-u23-africa-cup-of-nations/2023/news/morocco-win-maiden-totalenergies-u-23-africa-cup-of-nations-title-with-victory-o |access-date=9 July 2023 |website=CAFOnline.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 July 2023 |title=Le Mali, le Maroc et l'Égypte qualifiés pour les JO 2024 |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/le-mali-le-maroc-et-legypte-qualifies-pour-les-jo-2024 |access-date=9 July 2023 |website=SO FOOT.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

Ezzalzouli was selected for Morocco's squad to compete in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|men's football]] at the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-07-04 |title=Morocco's Head Coach unveils squad list for 2024 Olympic Games |url=https://en.hespress.com/87471-moroccos-head-coach-unveils-squad-list-for-2024-olympic-games.html |access-date=2024-07-18 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, Ezzalzouli was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

